00:00:29.179 --> 00:00:31.660
Lisa from Malawi stated,

00:00:31.660 --> 00:00:40.340
With this convention, I saw how Jehovah fulfilled his promise at Hebrews chapter 13 verse 5.

00:00:40.340 --> 00:00:46.299
I will never leave you, and I will never abandon you.

00:00:46.299 --> 00:00:52.219
Many have made similar appreciative comments after watching the Convention in their language.

00:00:52.219 --> 00:01:00.299
You have made kind donations online at donate.jw.org, and by other means.

00:01:00.299 --> 00:01:08.030
Thank you for these donations that support our extensive translation efforts.

00:01:08.030 --> 00:01:14.750
Earlier in our program, we discussed five piece records that we should put away.

00:01:14.750 --> 00:01:18.870
But what can we do if peace has been disturbed?

00:01:18.870 --> 00:01:20.989
Can it be restored?

00:01:20.989 --> 00:01:23.349
And if so, how?

00:01:23.349 --> 00:01:29.390
We invite you to pay careful attention to the following four-part symposium.

00:01:29.390 --> 00:01:36.109
Brother John Ekran, a helper to the coordinators committee, will start us off with the talk,

00:01:36.109 --> 00:01:49.439
seek peace and pursue it, by not quickly taking offense.

00:01:49.439 --> 00:01:55.480
The title of this series of four talks is Seek, Peace, and Pursuit, and it's based

00:01:55.560 --> 00:01:58.280
on 1 Peter chapter 3 and verse 11.

00:01:58.280 --> 00:02:00.680
Let's read that together.

00:02:00.680 --> 00:02:05.769
1 Peter chapter 3 and verse 11.

00:02:05.769 --> 00:02:09.969
Let him turn away from what is bad, and do what is good.

00:02:09.969 --> 00:02:15.090
Let him seek peace and pursue it.

00:02:15.090 --> 00:02:21.090
Yes, we have to pursue peace, and pursuit requires effort.

00:02:21.090 --> 00:02:26.810
If you ever had to chase a piece of paper that was in your hands and got blown away by the wind,

00:02:26.810 --> 00:02:32.009
and just when you get to it, the wind blows it away again and again, it can really take

00:02:32.009 --> 00:02:37.050
quite some effort to retrieve and get that paper back in your hands.

00:02:37.050 --> 00:02:42.729
Just standing there and watching the paper blow further and further away is not going

00:02:42.729 --> 00:02:45.169
to get it back.

00:02:45.169 --> 00:02:47.969
Well peace can be a lot like that paper.

00:02:47.969 --> 00:02:54.810
At some point, it can get blown away, and we have to then chase or pursue it to get

00:02:54.810 --> 00:02:58.050
that piece back again.

00:02:58.050 --> 00:03:04.409
This series of talks will help us to pursue peace in four ways, by not quickly taking

00:03:04.409 --> 00:03:16.250
offense, by apologizing, by forgiving freely, and by using our gift of speech wisely.

00:03:16.250 --> 00:03:24.050
Let's consider our first way to pursue peace, avoid quickly taking offense.

00:03:24.050 --> 00:03:30.289
Now because we are imperfect, we might misjudge others and quickly take offense.

00:03:30.289 --> 00:03:32.650
Notice that we say quickly take offense.

00:03:32.650 --> 00:03:34.449
That's an important word.

00:03:34.449 --> 00:03:42.189
We need to avoid jumping to conclusions quickly before we actually have the facts.

00:03:42.189 --> 00:03:47.310
Even faithful men like Jesus apostles have taken offense too quickly.

00:03:47.310 --> 00:03:51.669
You may recall the time that Jesus and His apostles were looking for lodging in a Samaritan

00:03:51.669 --> 00:03:53.189
village.

00:03:53.189 --> 00:03:58.310
Now the Samaritans in that village rudely denied them lodging.

00:03:58.310 --> 00:04:06.710
At Luke 9 verses 54 through 56, the apostles James and John say to Jesus, Lord, do you

00:04:06.710 --> 00:04:11.949
want us to call fire down from heaven and annihilate them?

00:04:11.949 --> 00:04:18.319
But Jesus rebukes them for their rash and rather violent suggestion.

00:04:18.319 --> 00:04:23.439
Luke of the serious consequences had Jesus yielded to the violent temper of James and

00:04:23.439 --> 00:04:24.959
John.

00:04:24.959 --> 00:04:29.439
The Samaritans could have become prejudiced against the kingdom message.

00:04:29.439 --> 00:04:34.240
Instead, Jesus pursues a peaceful solution.

00:04:34.240 --> 00:04:38.040
The account says they simply went to a different village.

00:04:38.040 --> 00:04:42.480
Now, does this mean we're saying I can never take offense?

00:04:42.480 --> 00:04:46.800
No, you may have a legitimate cause for complaint.

00:04:46.800 --> 00:04:55.680
The key point is that we should not quickly draw conclusions before we hear all the facts.

00:04:55.680 --> 00:04:59.399
Proverbs chapter 18 and verse 13 says,

00:04:59.399 --> 00:05:07.689
When anyone replies to a matter before he hears the facts, it is foolish and humiliating.

00:05:07.689 --> 00:05:15.500
In the following dramatization, know what helps one sister to overlook an offense.

00:05:15.500 --> 00:05:17.899
And they expected more from you.

00:05:17.899 --> 00:05:20.220
Haley, what are you talking about?

00:05:20.220 --> 00:05:23.699
Got to pin about my posts.

00:05:23.699 --> 00:05:30.910
