00:06:19.699 --> 00:06:31.670
Some days I just feel so alone between Nana and work.

00:06:31.670 --> 00:06:35.829
And then knowing all of you were talking about me.

00:06:35.870 --> 00:06:40.860
I promise that's not what happened.

00:06:40.860 --> 00:06:46.199
You're just really tired and overwhelmed.

00:06:46.199 --> 00:06:50.629
So why don't we just slow things down a little?

00:06:50.629 --> 00:06:58.670
You know, meetings always make me feel better, even on my worst days.

00:06:58.670 --> 00:07:04.829
Why don't we go inside, clean up a little, enjoy the program together.

00:07:04.829 --> 00:07:08.589
Then afterwards, we can all talk.

00:07:08.589 --> 00:07:17.269
I promise it'll be okay.

00:07:17.269 --> 00:07:19.790
Haley really was upset.

00:07:19.790 --> 00:07:25.550
She'd already concluded that she was being gossiped about by everyone.

00:07:25.550 --> 00:07:33.069
If we find ourselves like Haley feeling offended, how can we avoid quickly taking offense?

00:07:33.069 --> 00:07:36.790
Well we must stop and think.

00:07:36.790 --> 00:07:43.310
Let's read Ecclesiastes chapter 7 and verse 9 for some very good advice in these situations.

00:07:43.310 --> 00:07:49.910
Ecclesiastes chapter 7 and verse 9 do not be quick to take offense.

00:07:49.910 --> 00:07:56.139
For the taking of offense lodges in the bosom of fools.

00:07:56.139 --> 00:08:02.139
Like Celia said in the parking lot to Haley, please calm down.

00:08:02.139 --> 00:08:07.579
So in those situations, we need to think about what you know and just as importantly what

00:08:07.579 --> 00:08:09.579
you don't know.

00:08:09.779 --> 00:08:15.620
You know what you were told happened, but what was really said?

00:08:15.620 --> 00:08:19.259
In the video, Haley quickly believed what she was told.

00:08:19.259 --> 00:08:24.019
She did not even ask Celia what she really said.

00:08:24.019 --> 00:08:30.370
Or you may know what was said, but do you know what was really meant by it?

00:08:30.370 --> 00:08:33.409
Haley asked, did you talk about my posts?

00:08:33.409 --> 00:08:39.789
And Celia said yes, and immediately Haley assumed the worst.

00:08:39.789 --> 00:08:44.029
Or perhaps we misjudged the person who heard us.

00:08:44.029 --> 00:08:50.830
Haley misjudged Celia on the spot by saying, you're just as bad as Emily.

00:08:50.830 --> 00:08:54.629
She had not even heard from Celia yet.

00:08:54.629 --> 00:08:59.389
Haley said to Celia, she was the mature one, the one she looked up to.

00:08:59.389 --> 00:09:03.230
And yet she was quick to believe the worst about her.

00:09:03.230 --> 00:09:10.009
Haley had not stopped and really thought about what she was thinking and saying.

00:09:10.009 --> 00:09:13.409
Perhaps she was having a hard day.

00:09:13.409 --> 00:09:17.090
Well Celia really set a fine example for us.

00:09:17.090 --> 00:09:23.330
Even though Haley spoke harshly to her, Celia was calm and listened to Haley.

00:09:23.330 --> 00:09:28.490
As Haley explained how she was feeling lonely, dealing and caring for her grandmother,

00:09:28.490 --> 00:09:33.730
you can see the love and concern that Celia had for Haley, even though just moments before

00:09:33.730 --> 00:09:38.090
she had spoken really harshly to her.

00:09:38.090 --> 00:09:44.809
Well besides taking time to think things through, we also need to remember that it is Jehovah's

00:09:44.809 --> 00:09:47.809
opinion of us that matters the most.

00:09:47.809 --> 00:09:53.809
Now, that's an important point, especially when we deal with misunderstandings or false

00:09:53.809 --> 00:09:56.649
accusations.

00:09:56.649 --> 00:09:58.169
Think about it.

00:09:58.169 --> 00:10:02.049
Jehovah is an eyewitness to everything.

00:10:02.049 --> 00:10:05.129
Dilustrate that I want you to imagine.

00:10:05.129 --> 00:10:06.649
You had a traffic accident.

00:10:06.649 --> 00:10:12.490
Now you were just sitting at the stop sign, but another car ran straight into you.

00:10:12.490 --> 00:10:20.529
Now, police come and the person that ran into you says that you ran into them and the police

00:10:20.529 --> 00:10:23.129
believed them.

00:10:23.129 --> 00:10:25.409
You take the matter to court.

00:10:25.409 --> 00:10:26.409
The judge listens.

00:10:26.409 --> 00:10:33.210
As the other person says that you ran into them, however, before you can say anything, the

00:10:33.210 --> 00:10:37.690
judge says, no, that is not what happened.

00:10:37.690 --> 00:10:43.129
I was there walking on the sidewalk across the street that day and I saw the whole thing.

00:10:43.129 --> 00:10:49.860
Well, it's extremely likely that you can go to court and expect the judge for your case

00:10:49.860 --> 00:10:52.460
to have been an eyewitness.

00:10:52.460 --> 00:10:56.659
This does illustrate, though, the peace of mind that we can have knowing that Jehovah

00:10:56.659 --> 00:11:01.139
is an eyewitness to all that happens.

00:11:01.139 --> 00:11:08.460
So when falsely accused, or we have a misunderstanding that we cannot seem to clear up, it is of great

00:11:08.460 --> 00:11:16.980
comfort for us to know that Jehovah was there that day and saw the whole thing.

00:11:16.980 --> 00:11:22.700
We don't need to take offense at every negative thing that is said or done around us or feel

00:11:22.700 --> 00:11:28.179
we have to defend ourselves as right on every occasion.

00:11:28.179 --> 00:11:36.600
We would surely wear out emotionally and probably not have very many friends.

00:11:36.600 --> 00:11:41.519
We should be willing to overlook minor transgressions.

00:11:41.519 --> 00:11:46.639
Let's look at Proverbs 19 and verse 11.

00:11:46.639 --> 00:11:52.320
Proverbs 19 and verse 11, what can help us?

00:11:52.320 --> 00:11:57.919
The insight of a man certainly slows down his anger.

00:11:57.919 --> 00:12:03.960
And it is beauty on his part to overlook an offense.

00:12:03.960 --> 00:12:07.519
So can you overlook an offense?

00:12:07.519 --> 00:12:11.759
As the Proverbs said, that is beauty on our part.

00:12:11.759 --> 00:12:18.879
If not and you have a serious cause for complaint, handle matters according to Jehovah's direction,

00:12:18.879 --> 00:12:24.600
show insight, slow down any anger.

00:12:24.600 --> 00:12:31.320
Take carefully and listen patiently to make sure you clearly have all the facts before

00:12:31.320 --> 00:12:35.590
you become offended or take action.

00:12:35.590 --> 00:12:41.070
Remember that piece of paper that you had in your hands and got blown away by the wind?

00:12:41.070 --> 00:12:44.990
What if it was a hundred dollar bill?

00:12:44.990 --> 00:12:50.909
You would make every effort to pursue it and get it back because it is valuable.

00:12:50.909 --> 00:12:55.950
Our piece with our brothers is far more valuable than paper money.

00:12:55.950 --> 00:13:01.269
When our piece with our brothers or sisters is blown away by misunderstandings, mistakes,

00:13:01.269 --> 00:13:04.629
or sin, then you should pursue peace.

00:13:04.629 --> 00:13:08.409
Try hard to get it back.

00:13:08.409 --> 00:13:17.789
Yes, we glorify God and promote peace when we avoid quickly taking offense.

00:13:17.789 --> 00:13:21.909
Brother Ralph Walls, a helper to the Personnel Committee, will now present the next talk

00:13:21.909 --> 00:13:35.659
of this symposium, seek peace and pursue it by apologizing.

00:13:35.659 --> 00:13:39.379
I am so sorry.

00:13:39.379 --> 00:13:42.779
It's my fault, please forgive me.

00:13:42.779 --> 00:13:48.100
No matter how we phrase it, it can be difficult to apologize.

00:13:48.100 --> 00:13:50.500
Why is that so challenging?

00:13:50.500 --> 00:13:52.340
There are many reasons.

00:13:52.340 --> 00:13:56.259
We may fear confrontation, lame or rejection.

00:13:56.259 --> 00:13:59.620
Perhaps we feel embarrassed and we are too proud to apologize.

00:13:59.620 --> 00:14:04.820
We may reason, apologizing will not undo the blunder I have already made.

00:14:04.820 --> 00:14:09.139
And it may even be that we are angry.

00:14:09.139 --> 00:14:17.100
This is such a matter of concern that in July 2000, the California State Legislature in

00:14:17.100 --> 00:14:23.100
the United States passed a bill designed to relieve people of liability if they express

00:14:23.100 --> 00:14:27.299
sympathy to an individual who was injured in an accident in which they themselves were

00:14:27.299 --> 00:14:29.139
involved.

00:14:29.139 --> 00:14:33.539
It was noted that people often hesitate to extend an apology out of concern that it

00:14:33.539 --> 00:14:39.220
could be construed in court as an admission of guilt.

00:14:39.220 --> 00:14:46.419
The Bible provides an account of a faithful servant, the Apostle Paul, who was a good example

00:14:46.419 --> 00:14:49.059
of one who apologized.

00:14:49.059 --> 00:14:53.139
The account is in the Book of Acts, chapter 23.

00:14:53.139 --> 00:15:01.059
The setting, a Roman military officer wanted to know why Paul was being accused by the Jews.

00:15:01.059 --> 00:15:08.299
So he brought Paul to the Jewish chief priests and commanded the Sanhedrin, the high court,

00:15:08.299 --> 00:15:10.100
to assemble.

00:15:10.100 --> 00:15:16.379
As we read Acts chapter 23 verses 1 through 5 together, we can't help but be impressed

00:15:16.379 --> 00:15:20.379
by Paul's boldness as he stands for what is right.

00:15:20.379 --> 00:15:26.379
But at the same time, please take note of his humility.

00:15:26.379 --> 00:15:29.139
Acts 23.

00:15:29.139 --> 00:15:32.580
Looking intently at the Sanhedrin, Paul said,

00:15:32.580 --> 00:15:39.419
Men, brothers, I have behaved before God with a perfectly clear conscience down to this

00:15:39.419 --> 00:15:40.419
day.

00:15:40.419 --> 00:15:45.899
At this, the high priest and an I has ordered those standing by him to strike him on the

00:15:45.899 --> 00:15:46.899
mouth.

00:15:46.899 --> 00:15:53.100
Then Paul said to him, God is going to strike you, you white washed wool.

00:15:53.100 --> 00:15:58.419
Do you sit to judge me according to the law and at the same time violate the law by commanding

00:15:58.419 --> 00:16:01.059
me to be struck?

00:16:01.059 --> 00:16:08.019
Those standing by said, are you insulting the high priest of God?

00:16:08.019 --> 00:16:13.460
And Paul said, brothers, I did not know he was high priest.

00:16:13.460 --> 00:16:20.649
For it is written, you must not speak injuriously of a ruler of your people.

00:16:20.649 --> 00:16:24.210
Paul immediately admitted his error.

00:16:24.210 --> 00:16:30.409
And he had said that the one appointed as judge should not resort to violence was right.

00:16:30.409 --> 00:16:34.090
Yet he apologized.

00:16:34.090 --> 00:16:39.169
In the following dramatization, we will see an older sister applying the inspired words

00:16:39.169 --> 00:16:45.210
of Titus chapter 2 verses 3 through 5 in order to advise younger sisters to be sound

00:16:45.210 --> 00:16:47.250
in mind.

00:16:47.250 --> 00:16:52.889
We will also observe how one of the younger sisters avoids further problems and pursues

00:16:52.889 --> 00:17:05.380
peace by humbly apologising.

00:17:05.380 --> 00:17:13.660
I don't know how this happened, but Haley, I'm sorry.

00:17:13.660 --> 00:17:23.210
It hurts me to see you so upset, if you too.

