All this drama, let's stop, come on, girls, Haley, come closer.

00:17:59.900 --> 00:18:18.390
Love is patient and kind, it's not jealous.

00:18:18.390 --> 00:18:26.390
It doesn't become provoked, even when things become difficult.

00:18:26.390 --> 00:18:32.190
So what are we going to do?

00:18:32.190 --> 00:18:37.390
I just thought they've been.

00:18:37.390 --> 00:18:47.450
No, I'm sorry, Haley.

00:18:47.450 --> 00:19:01.509
I'm sorry, I shouldn't have judged you so harshly, I shouldn't have judged you at all,

00:19:01.509 --> 00:19:07.779
and I'm sorry for dragging you into this, but twisting what you said.

00:19:07.779 --> 00:19:11.420
It's okay, things happen.

00:19:11.420 --> 00:19:20.809
I've been on both ends.

00:19:20.809 --> 00:19:30.329
I should never have spoken that way to you, Celia.

00:19:30.329 --> 00:19:39.859
To either of you, I'm to know.

00:19:39.859 --> 00:19:51.960
I'll call you tomorrow.

00:19:51.960 --> 00:19:56.759
The older sister apologized, even though she was not in the wrong.

00:19:56.759 --> 00:20:01.519
She also urged the two younger sisters to make peace.

00:20:01.519 --> 00:20:07.200
It takes courage, humility, and determination to apologize.

00:20:07.200 --> 00:20:16.349
It's interesting to know what stated at Philippians 2 and verse 3.

00:20:16.349 --> 00:20:21.470
Do nothing out of contentiousness or out of egotism.

00:20:21.470 --> 00:20:27.750
But with humility, consider others superior to you.

00:20:27.750 --> 00:20:33.910
That means our determined effort is not to win an argument, which could be contentious.

00:20:33.910 --> 00:20:38.789
Nor do we want to start a discussion with the primary thought being that we are in the

00:20:38.789 --> 00:20:44.269
right, that mean that we are self-concerned or egotistical.

00:20:44.269 --> 00:20:51.430
Rather, in harmony with the principle of that scripture, we want to act with humility.

00:20:52.430 --> 00:20:56.029
Our aim should be to pursue peace.

00:20:56.029 --> 00:21:02.950
Even if we think the other person is being unreasonable, we apologize.

00:21:02.950 --> 00:21:06.109
Why is it so important to do so?

00:21:06.109 --> 00:21:11.390
Because that is what makes our worship to Jehovah acceptable.

00:21:11.390 --> 00:21:21.880
At Matthew chapter 5, verses 23 and 24, Jesus makes it very clear.

00:21:21.920 --> 00:21:26.559
If then, you are bringing your gift to the altar.

00:21:26.559 --> 00:21:30.880
And there you remember that your brother has something against you.

00:21:30.880 --> 00:21:36.480
Leave your gift there in front of the altar and go away.

00:21:36.480 --> 00:21:40.440
First, make your peace with your brother.

00:21:40.440 --> 00:21:45.519
And then come back and offer your gift.

