00:44:11.909 --> 00:44:19.349
My first thought, oh no, here we go again. I've seen this movie before.

00:44:20.230 --> 00:44:24.070
You don't think she's showing off? Is this just about Ellie?

00:44:26.309 --> 00:44:31.510
Seems it's all about Ellie. Is there just a little bit of envy in there?

00:44:35.400 --> 00:44:45.320
I've lived it. If it's the case of her being more careful how she comes across, that's another matter.

00:44:45.320 --> 00:44:51.559
What did she suggest? I should tell her that she needs to stop.

00:44:51.559 --> 00:44:56.840
Can you believe that? Especially as a pioneer. What kind of example is this?

00:44:56.840 --> 00:44:59.159
How quickly it snowballs out of control.

00:45:00.840 --> 00:45:07.219
You are such lonely. You've got nothing better to do.

00:45:07.699 --> 00:45:19.210
How difficult it can be to unravel.

00:45:30.840 --> 00:45:34.519
A chance to forgive is a chance to imitate your hover.

00:45:36.039 --> 00:45:39.239
Think back to a time when you wanted forgiveness.

00:45:47.579 --> 00:45:51.500
Has anyone ever tried talking to her about her singing?

00:45:55.739 --> 00:46:00.940
You know what I love about Baroneca? She's probably the most hospitable person I know.

00:46:01.500 --> 00:46:06.860
Always open house at her place. And can she cook? Have you tried her curry?

00:46:21.420 --> 00:46:25.980
We should use our gift of speech to honor God and to benefit others.

00:46:27.019 --> 00:46:33.340
And if somebody gets angry at us, our mild reply can diffuse the situation.

00:46:34.139 --> 00:46:42.940
As Proverbs 151 says, a mild answer turns away rage, but a harsh word stirs up anger.

00:46:44.139 --> 00:46:48.940
We can also use our gift of speech to console and encourage others.

